<title>USA: Phibro ends coal, coke, fertilizer trading.</title>
<headline>Phibro ends coal, coke, fertilizer trading.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Salomon Inc said its Phibro unit is ceasing its coal, coke and fertilizer trading operations under a plan to reduce headcount at the unit by about 20 percent.</p>
<p>Salomon spokesman Robert Baker said Phibro's oils, metals and soft commodities activities remain unchanged. He said the firm did not expect costs associated with the move would be material to coming quarters.  </p>
<p>About 80 Phibro employees are affected by the move, Baker said.  He could not immediately provide further specifics, such as the locations of affected employees or the degree to which Phibro's other trading areas might be affected.</p>
<p>-- Wall Street desk, 212-859-1730</p>
